    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Curaçoa</placeName>
                <date>April 27<hi rend="sup">th</hi>.1857</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">I am in possession of the Bible<lb/> $4 at your credit and also of
                your short but kind<lb/> favor. Believe me I heartily sympathize with you<lb/> and
                did I enjoy the pleasure of a more intimate acquaintance<lb/> would take the liberty
                of assisting<add>?</add> you, since you have been so<lb/> long and so unweariedly
                fighting the battles of true religion<lb/> and consistency, you should now retire
                from the field<lb/> and you can do so with the pleasing consciousness that<lb/> you
                have not only diligently but successfully struggled<lb/> for the faith. Let others
                now buckle on the armour. A<lb/> man owes certain duties to himself. The vice of modern<lb/>
                <add>?</add>torship is to sacrifice. Truth and Gentlemanly conduct<lb/> the
                smartness; ably described in <persName>Bulwer's</persName> “<persName>Paul
                    Clifford</persName>”<lb/> The synagogue has taken wide and deep roots in the
                    <placeName>U S.</placeName><lb/> and the modern fashionable Pantheism with
                all<lb/> the other crazy German “Isms” will not prevail against it<lb/> Tender our
                kind regards to <persName>Mr E Moses</persName>
                <persName>Mr<lb/> Lobo</persName> &amp; family and accept the same from yours
                truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(11)">
                <persName role="author">Henry Nathan</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
